               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Daily Office Prayers and Litanies (fols. 3ra-14vb)
 II) Śǝrʿāta
                     qǝddāse “Ordinary of the Mass” (fols. 14vb-34va)
 III) Anaphoras (fols.
                     35ra-115rb)
 III-1) Anaphora of the Apostles (fols. 35ra-47rb)
 III-2)
                     Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ (fols. 48ra-51ra), preceded by an excerpt
                     from “Testament of Our Lord” (fols. 47rb-48ra)
 III-3) Anaphora of Our Lady
                     by St Cyriacus of Behnesa (fols. 51ra-59vb)
 III-4) Anaphora of St John,
                     Son of Thunder (fols. 59vb-66vb)
 III-5) Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox
                     Fathers of Nicaea (fols. 66vb-72va)
 III-6) Anaphora of St John Chrysostom
                     (fols. 72va-77va)
 III-7) Anaphora of St Epiphanius of Cyprus (fols.
                     77va-82ra)
 III-8) Anaphora of St Gregory (“Hosanna-liturgy of St Gregory’)
                     (fols. 82ra-86va)
 III-9) Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug (fols.
                     86va-91rb)
 III-10) Anaphora of St Athanasius of Alexandria (fols.
                     91rb-100rb)
 III-11) Anaphora of St Basil of Caesarea (fols.
                     100rb-107vb)
 III-12) Anaphora of St Cyril of Alexandria (fols.
                     107vb-113ra)
 III-13) Second Anaphora of St Gregory (fols.
                     113ra-115rb)
 
 Additiones 1-3.</summary>
