                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#2va">f. 2va</locus>
                           <desc>: List of the Ethiopic Anaphoras.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Crudely written in red ink. Some of the Anaphoras are named either
                              according to their incipits or according to the liturgical occasions
                              on which they are celebrated. The number and sequence of the Anaphoras
                              in the list do not coincide with their number and sequence in the Ms.
                              A Tǝgrǝñña form (ናይ፡) is used in the name of the last Anaphora.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#2vb">f. 2vb</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#2vb">2vb</locus>: ዝመፅሀፍ፡ ዘመደ፡ ማርያም፡ ዘወሀበት፡ ለሚካኤል፡ በለሳ፡
                              ከመ፡ ይኩና፡ መርህ፡ ለመንግስተ፡ ሰማያት</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#2vb">2vb</locus>: This is a book (of) Zämädä Māryām
                              who donated it to (the church of) St Michael Bäläsa so that it might
                              be for her a guide to the Kingdom of Heaven.</quote>
                           <note> Crudely written in red ink in the same hand as Additio 1. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#115rb">f. 115rb</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#115rb">115rb</locus>: ዝመጽሃፍ፡ ዘገብረ፡ መድኅን፡ ወዘመደ፡ ማርያም፡
                              ዘተሳየጡ፡ በን&lt;ዋ&gt;ዮሙ። ዘወብዎ [sic]፡ ለሚካኤል፡</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#115rb">115rb</locus>: This is a book of Gabra Madḫǝn
                              and Zämädä Māryām who acquired it for their own money, who donated it
                              to (the church of St.) Michael.</quote>
                           <note> Crudely written. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Beginning of a recent purchase note, crudely written on
                              <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>: ዝመጽሐፈ፡ ቅዳሴ፡ ዘቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ዘተሳየጥዎ፡ በ፶ብር፡
                           “This is a Missal of (the church of) St Michael, which was bought for 50
                           Bǝrr”. Crude notes in green ink (possibly a continuation of the purchase
                           note) are added beside. Both texts are written upside down.
 - A
                           piece of parchment is sewn to fol. 3 (in the upper part) containing on
                           both sides the expected text. The following folios (fols. 4-10) have
                           triangular pieces of parchment sewn to their inner upper edges,
                           containing the needed text. The reason for the replacement of parchment
                           is unclear.
 - Crude notes: <locus target="#115v">115v</locus>.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
